

= scalable, censorship-resistant mirror network for the web


URL = http://mirrorparty.org

=Description=

Peter Fein:

"Where's the Party is a scalable, censorship-resistant mirror network
for the web. It aims to make mirroring more accessible for both
clients and hosts, allowing several orders of magnitude greater
participation. WTP is different from previous mirroring efforts
because it works entirely with software users already have - no
additional packages need to be installed for either clients or hosts.
 
WTP consists of software tools for building mirror networks and a
website for matching content with volunteer hosts. It operates by
using JavaScript in the browser to reconstruct the namespace that is a
website from content hosted on multiple servers."
 


